Package engine.forBoard

Class MoveTransition

java.lang.Object
engine.forBoard.MoveTransition
public final class MoveTransition extends Object
The `MoveTransition` class represents a transition between two chess board states resulting from a specific move. It encapsulates the information related to the source and destination boards, the transition move performed, and the status of the move, indicating whether it was successful, illegal, or resulted in leaving the player's king in check.
Author:
Aaron Ho
